This paper is primarily focused on machine learning and deep neural networks, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Additionally, the paper specifically applies its proposed Tensor Contraction Layer (TCL) to the task of image recognition, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-category. The use of tensor methods and decompositions also suggests that the paper may be relevant to the cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) sub-category. The paper's focus on neural network layers and end-to-end training suggests that it may also be relevant to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. Finally, the paper's use of data representations and multi-dimensional dependencies suggests that it may also be relevant to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category.
